class:: BassFaceCh
summary:: BYOD-derived heavy bass distortion model
categories:: UGens>Filters

Description::

BassFaceCh follows BYOD's public `Bass Face` model. The core DSP is a conditioned residual LSTM: for every sample, the network receives the audio sample together with the normalized `gain` control, updates its hidden state, and predicts a nonlinear output that is mixed in the same residual way as the source processor. Mathematically this is a nonlinear state-space model, so the tone depends not only on the current sample value but also on the recent signal history carried in the recurrent state.

The port keeps BYOD's public model assets and sample-rate strategy, including oversampled operation at standard project rates. Sonically this kind of model tends to sound thicker and more program-dependent than a memoryless shaper, with compression, sustain, and low-end behavior that change with playing dynamics rather than only with instantaneous amplitude.

